in` only finds the first checkpoint; remaining sessions are invisible\\n    11→4. Deleting the feature branch makes the original per-commit checkpoints unreachable\\n    12→\\n    13→Example squash commit message from GitHub:\\n    14→```\\n    15→Soph/test branch (#2)\\n    16→* random_letter script\\n    17→\\n    18→Entire-Checkpoint: 0aa0814d9839\\n    19→\\n    20→* random color\\n    21→\\n    22→Entire-Checkpoint: 33fb587b6fbb\\n    23→```\\n    24→\\n    25→## Design\\n    26→\\n    27→### Approach: Multi-checkpoint parsing in the resume flow\\n    28→\\n    29→The fix is localized to trailer parsing and the resume command. No changes to condensation, hooks, or the checkpoint storage format.\\n    30→\\n    31→### 1. Trailer Parsing (`trailers/trailers.go`)\\n    32→\\n    33→Add `ParseAllCheckpoints()` following the existing `ParseAllSessions()` pattern:\\n    34→- Uses `FindAllStringSubmatch` instead of `FindStringSubmatch`\\n    35→- Deduplicates checkpoint IDs while preserving order\\n    36→- Returns `[]checkpointID.CheckpointID`\\n    37→\\n    38→The existing `ParseCheckpoint()` (single-match) remains unchanged for callers that only need one.\\n    39→\\n    40→### 2. Checkpoint Discovery (`resume.go`)\\n    41→\\n    42→Change `branchCheckpointResult.checkpointID` (single) to `checkpointIDs` (slice).\\n    43→\\n    44→Update `findBranchCheckpoint` and `findCheckpointInHistory`:\\n    45→- Use `ParseAllCheckpoints()` instead of `ParseCheckpoint()`\\n    46→- The HEAD fast-path and history walk both collect all IDs from the first matching commit\\n    47→- Empty-check becomes `len(result.checkpointIDs) == 0`\\n    48→\\n    49→### 3. Resume Flow (`resume.go`)\\n    50→\\n    51→Single-checkpoint path (common case) stays identical — no behavior change. When `len(checkpointIDs) == 1`, the existing `resumeSession` flow is used.\\n    52→\\n    53→New `resumeMultipleCheckpoints` function for squash merge commits:\\n    54→1. Gets metadata branch tree (with remote fallback)\\n    55→2. Loops over checkpoint IDs, calling `ReadCheckpointMetadata` + `strat.RestoreLogsOnly` for each\\n    56→3. Skips checkpoints whose metadata isn't available (best-effort)\\n    57→4. Aggregates all restored sessions into a single slice\\n    58→5. Sorts by `CreatedAt` and displays resume commands\\n    59→\\n    60→Output matches existing multi-session format:\\n    61→```\\n    62→Restored 2 sessions. To continue, run:\\n    63→  claude --resume abc123  # implement random_letter script\\n    64→  claude --resume def456  # add random color (most recent)\\n    65→```\\n    66→\\n    67→## Scope\\n    68→\\n    69→### In scope\\n    70→- `trailers/trailers.go` — new `ParseAllCheckpoints()` function\\n    71→- `resume.go` — updated `branchCheckpointResult`, `findBranchCheckpoint`, `findCheckpointInHistory`, new `resumeMultipleCheckpoints`\\n    72→- Tests for all changed code\\n    73→\\n    74→### Out of scope\\n    75→- Dashboard visibility (separate concern)\\n    76→- Handling stripped/customized squash commit messages (best-effort: we work with available trailers)\\n    77→- Branch-not-found error messaging (keep existing behavior)\\n    78→- Changes to condensation, hooks, or checkpoint storage format\\n    79→\\n    80→## Edge Cases\\n    81→\\n    82→- **User customizes squash message and removes trailers**: Best effort — we can only find what's there. Same behavior as today (no checkpoint found).\\n    83→- **Some checkpoint metadata missing**: Skip those checkpoints, restore what we can.\\n    84→- **Single checkpoint in squash commit**: Falls through to existing single-checkpoint path, no behavior change.\\n    85→- **Non-squash commits**: Always have 0 or 1 trailer, existing behavior preserved.\\n    86→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"e01feba4-5d0e-4d94-8908-632b8dc8c2df\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T22:01:00.682Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ae7858bbc34ab153f\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_m