tores each session independently\\n- All sessions restored in chronological order with per-session resume commands\\n\\n**Key Implementation Detail:**\\nGitHub squash merge lists trailers in REVERSE chronological order (newest first in commit message), but `collectCheckpointsByAge()` sorts by `CreatedAt` ascending to restore oldest first, newest last—ensuring newest data wins on disk.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. KEY DATA STRUCTURES\\n\\n**branchCheckpointResult** (lines 306-313)\\n```go\\ntype branchCheckpointResult struct {\\n    checkpointIDs     []id.CheckpointID\\n    commitHash        string\\n    commitMessage     string\\n    newerCommitsExist bool\\n    newerCommitCount  int\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**RestoredSession** (strategy package)\\n```go\\ntype RestoredSession struct {\\n    SessionID string\\n    Agent     types.AgentType\\n    Prompt    string              // First prompt for display\\n    CreatedAt time.Time            // Used for sorting\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**RewindPoint** (strategy package)\\n```go\\ntype RewindPoint struct {\\n    IsLogsOnly   bool\\n    CheckpointID id.CheckpointID\\n    Agent        types.AgentType\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. IMPORTANT FUNCTIONS AND UTILITIES\\n\\n| Function | Purpose | Location |\\n|----------|---------|----------|\\n| `runResume` | Main entry point, handles branch checkout | 62-122 |\\n| `resumeFromCurrentBranch` | Checkpoint discovery and routing | 124-180 |\\n| `findBranchCheckpoints` | Finds checkpoints unique to branch (not on main) | 318-381 |\\n| `findCheckpointInHistory` | Walks commit history, distinguishes merge commits | 388-433 |\\n| `resumeMultipleCheckpoints` | Restores multiple checkpoints from squash merge | 182-255 |\\n| `collectCheckpointsByAge` | Sorts checkpoints by CreatedAt for correct restore order | 261-274 |\\n| `deduplicateSessions` | Merges sessions from multiple checkpoints | 279-304 |\\n| `displayRestoredSessions` | Prints resume commands, sorted by CreatedAt | 564-597 |\\n| `resumeSession` | Singl