eckpoint ID %q: must be 12 lowercase hex characters\\\", s)\\n    66→\\t}\\n    67→\\treturn nil\\n    68→}\\n    69→\\n    70→// String returns the checkpoint ID as a string.\\n    71→func (id CheckpointID) String() string {\\n    72→\\treturn string(id)\\n    73→}\\n    74→\\n    75→// IsEmpty returns true if the checkpoint ID is empty or unset.\\n    76→func (id CheckpointID) IsEmpty() bool {\\n    77→\\treturn id == EmptyCheckpointID\\n    78→}\\n    79→\\n    80→// Path returns the sharded path for this checkpoint ID on entire/checkpoints/v1.\\n    81→// Uses first 2 characters as shard (256 buckets), remaining as folder name.\\n    82→// Example: \\\"a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\" -> \\\"a3/b2c4d5e6f7\\\"\\n    83→func (id CheckpointID) Path() string {\\n    84→\\tif len(id) < 3 {\\n    85→\\t\\treturn string(id)\\n    86→\\t}\\n    87→\\treturn string(id[:2]) + \\\"/\\\" + string(id[2:])\\n    88→}\\n    89→\\n    90→// MarshalJSON implements json.Marshaler.\\n    91→func (id CheckpointID) MarshalJSON() ([]byte, error) {\\n    92→\\tdata, err := json.Marshal(string(id))\\n    93→\\tif err != nil {\\n    94→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to marshal checkpoint ID: %w\\\", err)\\n    95→\\t}\\n    96→\\treturn data, nil\\n    97→}\\n    98→\\n    99→// UnmarshalJSON implements json.Unmarshaler with validation.\\n   100→// Returns an error if the JSON string is not a valid 12-character hex ID.\\n   101→// Empty strings are allowed and result in EmptyCheckpointID.\\n   102→func (id *CheckpointID) UnmarshalJSON(data []byte) error {\\n   103→\\tvar s string\\n   104→\\tif err := json.Unmarshal(data, &s); err != nil {\\n   105→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to unmarshal checkpoint ID: %w\\\", err)\\n   106→\\t}\\n   107→\\t// Allow empty strings (represents unset checkpoint ID)\\n   108→\\tif s == \\\"\\\" {\\n   109→\\t\\t*id = EmptyCheckpointID\\n   110→\\t\\treturn nil\\n   111→\\t}\\n   112→\\tif err := Validate(s); err != nil {\\n   113→\\t\\treturn err\\n   114→